/-! ## P0 alignment tracker (machine-readable gap ledger)

The roadmap "Erdős 260 alignment roadmap" freezes the scope of the remaining
work as the task of **unconditionally inhabiting** the remaining provider fields
of the current strongest Appendix N chain-compression global input.  This section encodes the
audit conclusion as machine-readable Lean data so that every later phase has a
regression baseline: each manuscript dependency is tagged with one of four
alignment statuses, and each provider field is annotated with the phase that
closes it.
-/

/-- Alignment status of a manuscript item relative to a **fully unconditional**
Lean proof.

* `faithful` — a real, unconditional Lean theorem matching the manuscript.
* `conditional` — the obligation is currently encoded as a `structure` field
  (a hypothesis input that *is* the manuscript claim).
* `simplified` — a synthetic object stands in for the real manuscript object
  (e.g. `Fin L` for the Chernoff stopped tree, `range L` for the Kraft sum).
* `absent` — not yet formalized at all. -/
inductive AlignmentStatus where
  | faithful
  | conditional
  | simplified
  | absent
deriving DecidableEq, Repr

/-- One tracked manuscript dependency, recording where it lives in Lean, which
reduced provider field it ultimately feeds, and its current alignment status. -/
structure AlignmentItem where
  /-- Manuscript reference, e.g. `"Lemma 21.1"`, `"Appendix G.6"`. -/
  manuscriptTag : String
  /-- The reduced provider field this item feeds. -/
  provider : String
  /-- The Lean declaration or structure field carrying the obligation. -/
  leanName : String
  /-- Current alignment status. -/
  status : AlignmentStatus
  /-- The roadmap phase (`"P0"`..`"P10"`) that closes this item. -/
  phase : String
deriving DecidableEq, Repr

